experience has done much to reinforce my own class consciousness as a <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">member</ENAMEX> of
the latter <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">group</ENAMEX>. My <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">wife</ENAMEX> and I were minding our own business in an unregulated
apartment in the rapidly gentrifying <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">East Village</ENAMEX> when we returned from work
<TIMEX TYPE="DATE">one day</TIMEX> to a letter informing us that our already (to non-New <ENAMEX TYPE="NATIONALITY">Yorkers</ENAMEX>) alarming
rent of <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">$1,950</NUMEX> was going up <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">$700</NUMEX>. That's for a largish <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">one</NUMEX>-bedroom in a
